The ''Kleisli category'' of a [[Monad]] $$T$$ on $$\mathcal{C}$$, denoted $$Kl T$$ or $$\mathcal{C}_T$$, is the category:

* Objects are the objects of $$\mathcal{C}$$

* Morphisms are $$\mathcal{C}_T(A,B) := \mathcal{C}(A,TB)$$

